    "description": "This data set contains SWE data collected from the Reynolds Creek Experimental Watershed on 23 January 2020 and 23 February 2020 as part of the NASA SnowEx20 field campaign. Also available are raw point clouds of the snow surface from terrestrial laser scans (TLS) and RGB imagery from Unoccupied Aerial System (UAS) flights collected between 15 November 2018 and 23 February 2020. Real-time kinetic GNSS data is also provided for georeferencing the TLS point clouds and UAS imagery.",
